Unhelmed, he was, where stars glint in wet eyes,
No more appearing like something other.
Himself because he can now realise
a core importance that's now his tether.
"There are axioms of truth you can find -
some little pockets of stability
- which fight breakdowns of the entropic kind
But bring into you a fragility.
I want to think I know what comes, but then...
None can remember what's yet to happen"<==============
Among summer graves Spaceman grasped at strings
which puppeteered him back, set the sun.
What might have been sights that twilight oft brings
showed something walking out of void and none
like a subtraction to reality.
Spaceman saw, straight through horizon to space,
shaped-reflection of actuality,
a being that stayed cosmos from it's place
walked on legs of empty, it moved closer,
resting hand of nothing on his shoulder.<===========

"You'll find that you miss exhales in reverb
and thrice daily sunrise of satellites,"
it hummed through cosmic glows of far flung fogs,
where ionised dust darkly twist and turn
in tendrils with a thoughtless inertia,
spinning because it was spinning before.
"Eternal freefall like moon in orbit,
apart from thermodynamic chaos,
you found your home in upper vacancies."<=============

Hidden was broken asceticism
behind unsettled snowy mounds, like graves
of the thousand summers that never came
to the night-side of the Ever-Sunward.
Spaceman, having taken a mourning knee
so as to bring fight to pulling parachute
that follows the light-side sourced one-way wind,
sought the sun to keep the stars from his mind -
for
should he look up and reflect the stars,
he'd do the same for the spaces between.<========
The Spaceman fell from high-up stratosphere,
so heat had tunneled through ortho-fabrics.
Though braced and boldened, naught did atmos fear
neoprene and aramid synthetics
(As with the ortho-personality
which once had channeled, from hopeless despair
and built-up cynical mentality,
alleged inability to care).
Despite worn shells, this was a faceless fall;
pity for him, his helmet reflects all. <=========
Doubtless this was not without outliers
as the Discrete Timeline Viewer reacts
like chess moves from bots with eight by eight squares
imposed by logic of eight by eight mind,
ultimately led by human response.
Least of effects came from Rejectionists
rendered inert like opposite phased sines.
The Exchangers made moderate impact,
buffered out metastability by
active collapse of weak branches for strong.<=========
"These are my heroes: poor, broken losers.
The ones that do good and get forgotten.
I live for those forsaken by answers,
atoning for errors sans origin.
Named and few: if these no more existed,
you'd find the same in later substitutes
with traits imbued by mates who, unlisted,
helped to grind at thoughts of past destitutes.
For sure, times are better than before,
but only because that's what they strive for."
These words of Octo found way past the door
where Ram-man, under bundled wires, sat
to probe and test their tooling for what comes.
By electric fields of good intent,
prior to a knock the door was open.
Magnetic induction of such intent
attracts unlike - out of noise comes bad news,
Unexpected patterns risk low control.
All were friends, but historically speaking,
surprise extra visitors don't bode well.<======

"Spark adhesives, static sealant, quark plugs:
double rolls of each, slim-line packed, stack tracked.
particulate transceivers and torque jugs -
bombarded, irradiated and smacked.
All the usual beside one more thing,
shown unreliable with no off switch.
No damping factors for her voltage swing
could prevent that charged whine or ceaseless bitch.
But above denial she amplifies
noise-hidden and overlooked sighs and cries."<========
"I understand, you grew your horns when little,
where, as weapon, people touted your life
and actions therein to carve and whittle
your sonder mind to points, like past was knife.
When little, evolutionarily,
we used to find refuge in each other,
in others we trusted so readily
to sound warning and guard from predator.
It seems if threat cannot be found external,
We resort to history internal.<=======================
"With fewer to fear, safe in boxes
but in danger of bureaucratic gun,
We slyly eye neighbours, hackers, doxxers,
any that hold onto our mistakes done.
The currently built social policing
has assumptions of unashamed riches
with the power to guilt honest speaking
of fallible acts and impulsive twitches.
Please know I've tried to keep road spikes from brain.
I know cells in yours bring you enough pain."<========

Octo, Owl and Snake part - a rare event -
pushing forth Peacock of the Central East.
"I spoke too much as myself and Peacock,
it was just a matter of time," she said,
"I made my mistakes out of good intent
so they want to find me a hidden bed.
'What better than a shed beyond the graves,'
they thought, 'Ram-man of the north would sure help.'
But they - like me - worry for your comfort.
I'm the crowding you escaped in the cold.<============
1f
With these words, recluse and renegade fame
reside inside the wheeled, self-made cabin.
Vertical gardens camouflage the walls
O
n the border of ice-laden forest.
Tinged white snows and light glows that spark and pulse
through windows barely in sight of Octo,
Owl and Snake, make their path through summer graves
to high-rise pyramid: prisms tight-packed
for techno-pharoahs by wage-slave staunch,
Rectangles rising to triangle form.<===================

All this alight below the DTV -
A circuit board sky of static lightning
branching, diverging, remerging to see
what could give the future a tightening
with exabyte bounds. For some it purports
certainty spectrums or tech-pharoahs' will,
for most it speaks uncourageous comforts
of a tomorrow continuing still.
All seeing First Pyramid's projections,
recursively act predicted actions.<====================
The multi-branch nodes of quantised futures
seemed locked to levels of The Ironics.
Their bitstreams, unfed to mainline culture's
information drainpipe steeped with Stoics,
permits event fanning of outward change
that comes from those who change else in id's stead.
Commitment to prevent selfward estrange-
ment keeps the Ironics from being led.
It's revolutionary to resent
resigning to the current as content.<===============
As result of this constant resistance,
these three Ironics return to city
from the turbulent nightside snowfields
(With narrow miss of the Spaceman arrest)
to chaos around a burning tower -
One which hosts taking gambles on futures
unlikely but wistful (such bet when won
yields two-fold: money and then outlook).
Talking from broken window, like bet lost,
Southern Dog throws servers and reject-truth.
"Load-bearing spines - concavity accrued
from weighing signs of coming debt-filled
foreboding whines and the thoughts that ensued
furrowing lines of DTV yet tilled -
are not found among civility priests
and those receivers of special rewards
for willingness to exploit common beasts
like you and me who - unlike paltry lords -
find value inherent in extractee,
not extractor (this they'll say they don't see).
"They speak with wrong words like there's no difference
between what's apparent and inherent,
They say 'be grateful' but mean give penance,
'be civilised' but mean obedient.
It is thus from these external pressures
(and not from my own internal motives)
that I, in violence, seize these sutures
that try to hide wounds a wrong-speaker gives.
Once weak thread is wrought from haemophile cut
we might find a fix to seal the wound shut."<==========
After safe escape to centroid hideout
at half the height of pyramid apex,
Young Deer - horns and hands splayed like frayed wires -
delivered hindsight, irate and anxious:
"As thorough a demolition it was,
Southern Dog, sometimes carefulness is key.
Keep doors on hinges and use key given
to notice matched lock is one more floor up.
Safe are scam winnings the Den runs daily;
Weep did old men as their porn chatrooms crashed."<=====
"You'll seem real smart with half-cocked quiet
But I'm acted on not, I act on it!"
Dog wrests booze from bottle with teeth and grit,
"Faced with nonsense, I do naught but riot
as force patterned solely to have me quit
of course earned only my rage and my spit.
Regardless if fight has no benefit,
my single concern: contradict bullshit
so that this impetus may find circuit.
I'm fully-cocked bitch and ready to bang."<======
Octo reminds what they live to avoid,
"Reverent to your convictions most lacked,
We cannot wait, meteoroid in void,
Efficient error correction's post-act.
While craters leave lasting landmarks and ores,
Velocity vectors have large margins.
Distant beauty is held by meteors,
though light ephemeral, humbled hearkens
and holds the passing glory as impact
with progenetic deposit tract."<================
Determinist Forces breach with a blast -
having stalked since chance spotting in snow fields
after catching meteorite Spaceman.
Defensive manouvres from Owl and Snake,
struck swift and silent under smoke covers
which billowed from grenades and flame-throwers.
On insurgence retreat and Ironic
rendezvous, there was little difference found
at half-height centroid hideout save charred walls.
Left about the same save an Octo.<=================
Limbs bound in back of dim-lit transport holds
knocked-out Octo head on Spaceman shoulder.
Seated across, similarly bound, monk scolds
(wordlessly) finger-size, getting bolder
with intensity in picking his nose.
Each expect they're labour-prison destined,
the propensity of rulers, they 'spose.
Each longing for travel to be hastened
for varied reasons, one for a fast-track
to the end, one for the start, one for both.<==
